choices.text:
I am not a prime number.
I am between 20 and 40.
I am one more than a square number.
What number am I?
You are definitely not a prime number because you are an integer greater than 1 that has no positive divisors other than itself and 1. However, your description of being "one more than a square number" is vague as it does not provide any additional information about what numbers could be considered 'square'. In fact, the only natural numbers for which this statement would hold are 4 (which you are one less than), 9 (an integer squared and an odd multiple of 3), or 25.
